3 CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is entered into as of March 11, 2025 (the “Effective Date”), by and between NICHOLAS COUNTY SOLAR PROJECT, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Nicholas”) and DEEP LAKE ENERGY CENTER, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Deep Lake”). Each of Nicholas and Deep Lake are referred to herein individually as a “Party,” and collectively as the “Parties.” RECITALS: A. Nicholas intends to construct and own and operate a 100 MW solar energy generation facility located in Nicholas County, West Virginia with associated collection circuits and interconnection lines and substation and related facilities and improvements (the “Nicholas Project”). B. Subsequent to the construction of the Nicholas Project, Deep Lake intends to construct, own and operate an approximately 150 MW solar energy generation facility with associated collection lines and related facilities and improvements (the “Deep Lake Project”) in proximity to the Nicholas Project. Together, the Nicholas Project and the Deep Lake Project, to the extent constructed, are referred to collectively as the “Projects”, and individually as a “Project”. C. As part of the Nicholas Project, Nicholas intends to construct certain high-voltage facilities, including; (i) a 34 kV collector substation yard with associated equipment and 138 kV substation yard with associated equipment, including a 138-34 kV main power transformer, circuit breakers, high voltage buswork, metering, conductors and substation control house, and communication equipment (collectively, the “Nicholas Substation”), and (ii) a 138 kV interconnection line with associated fiber optic cable and other associated facilities (the “Gen-Tie Line”) that extends approximately 300 feet from the Nicholas Substation to the Point of Change of Ownership (as defined below), thereby connecting the Nicholas Project to the transmission system owned by Monongahela Power Company (“MPC”), and the balancing authority area controlled by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (together with any successor authority, “PJM”), with such Nicholas Substation and Gen-Tie Line connecting to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to, and as defined in, that certain Generation Interconnection Agreement by and among Nicholas, MPC, and PJM dated January 24, 2025 (the “Nicholas GIA”), and that certain Generator Interconnection Agreement by and among Deep Lake, MPC, and PJM dated February 3, 2025 (the “Deep Lake GIA” and together with the Nicholas GIA, each a “GIA” and collectively the “GIAs.”). D. PJM is the Transmission Operator (“TOP”), as registered with the North American Electric Reliability Corporation (“NERC”), of the transmission system at the Point of Interconnection. E. Pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, Deep Lake intends to and shall have the right to construct new switching facilities within the Nicholas Substation (the “Deep Lake Switching Facilities”), which, when connected to the Shared Switching Facilities (as defined below), will be Docusign Envelope ID: 76F91F61-291A-48AE-A447-72386FFA8246
4 used as a point of common coupling of the Nicholas Project and the Deep Lake Project and to electrically tie both Projects into the Gen-Tie Line. The equipment and improvements to be shared between the Nicholas Project and the Deep Lake Project and the facilities for the exclusive use of each of the Nicholas Project and Deep Lake Project are depicted on Exhibit A attached hereto. F. Pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, and in accordance with plans and specifications approved by Nicholas, Deep Lake will directly contract with a construction contractor to install improvements at the Nicholas Substation to allow electrical connection of the Deep Lake Switching Facilities (the newly-constructed Nicholas Substation high-voltage bus expansion in addition to the existing Nicholas Substation high-voltage facilities that are necessary to connect the Deep Lake Switching Facilities to the Gen-Tie Line are hereafter referred to as the “Shared Switching Facilities”). The equipment and improvements that comprise the Shared Switching Facilities are further described and depicted on Exhibit A. The Shared Switching Facilities shall be located on a parcel of land that will be leased to Nicholas and Deep Lake as co-tenants pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, as generally depicted on Exhibit A-1 attached hereto (the “Shared Switching Facilities Parcel”). G. Deep Lake desires to install, own, and operate, and will directly contract with a construction contractor to install, a 138 kV overhead line to connect the Deep Lake Project to the Shared Facilities (the “Deep Lake Gen-Tie Line”), a portion of which will be constructed over and across real property leased and/or owned by Nicholas as part of the Nicholas Project. H. The integration and connection of the Deep Lake Switching Facilities and the Shared Switching Facilities will enable the Nicholas Project and the Deep Lake Project to have shared access to and use of the Gen-Tie Line between the Shared Switching Facilities up to the Point of Change of Ownership (which through the Transmission Owner interconnection facilities connect to the Point of Interconnection), in order to connect pursuant to the GIAs to reflect a shared Gen- Tie Line between Nicholas and Deep Lake as contemplated in this Agreement. I. Upon completion by Deep Lake of the Deep Lake Switching Facilities and Deep Lake Gen-Tie Line, Nicholas desires to permit Deep Lake to have access to and use of the Shared Switching Facilities and the Gen-Tie Line upon the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement. Upon completion by Deep Lake of the Deep Lake Switching Facilities and the expansion of the Nicholas Substation high-voltage bus, the Gen-Tie Line and the Shared Switching Facilities thereafter will be collectively referred to as the “Shared Facilities”. The Shared Facilities shall not include the portion of the Nicholas Substation not part of the Shared Switching Facilities, the Deep Lake Gen-Tie Line and the Deep Lake Switching Facilities. J. Subject to the terms contained herein, the Parties desire for Nicholas and Deep Lake to co-own the Shared Facilities, and for Nicholas and Deep Lake to have joint-use or overlapping easements (as to the Shared Facilities and Shared Switching Facilities Parcel) in order for Nicholas and Deep Lake to jointly use and operate the Shared Switching Facilities and the Gen-Tie Line from the Shared Switching Facilities Parcel to the Point of Change of Ownership (the “Shared Property Rights”). 5 K. The Parties wish to set forth herein their respective rights and obligations regarding such ownership of the Shared Property Rights and the Shared Facilities, and regarding the co-ownership use, operation, maintenance, repair, replacement of, and alterations to, the Shared Facilities. L. The Parties also wish to provide for the appointment of a manager of the Shared Facilities in order to provide certain services with respect to the Shared Facilities (the “Manager”) pursuant to an agreement between the Parties and such Manager, with the initial agreement to be executed by and between the Parties and Nicholas (the “Initial Manager”) pursuant to a form of manager agreement mutually acceptable to the Parties (the “Manager Agreement”). M. The Parties desire to set forth herein their respective duties, responsibilities and obligations relating to the operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities.
